### 05 · Alembic Migrations

<div class="not-prose flex gap-2 mb-3">
  <span class="font-mono text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-950 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Python</span>
  <span class="font-mono text-xs bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-950 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 px-2 py-0.5 rounded">PostgreSQL</span>
</div>

*Initialize Alembic and generate the initial migration from your SQLAlchemy models.*

#### Alembic setup

Alembic manages schema migrations. Unlike Drizzle Kit, you own the migration files completely — always review generated migrations before running them. Use async migrations with `asyncpg`.

<div class="not-prose my-4 rounded-r-lg border-l-2 border-emerald-500 bg-emerald-50 dark:bg-emerald-950 px-4 py-3 text-sm">
  <div class="mb-1 font-mono text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400">tip</div>
  <p class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Learn these 3 Alembic commands and run them yourself — never ask Claude to manage migrations. It will make mistakes.</p>
</div>

#### Initialize Alembic

```bash
cd backend
alembic init alembic
```

#### alembic/env.py — key changes needed

```python
# Replace the run_migrations_offline and run_migrations_online
# functions with async versions, and import your models:

from app.db import DATABASE_URL
from app.models.models import Base  # import all models
import asyncio
from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine

# In env.py, set:
target_metadata = Base.metadata

# Update the DATABASE_URL in alembic.ini OR set it dynamically:
config.set_main_option("sqlalchemy.url", DATABASE_URL)
```

#### Generate and run initial migration

```bash
# Generate migration from current models
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "initial schema"

# Review the generated file in alembic/versions/
# Then apply it:
alembic upgrade head
```

#### Common Alembic commands

```bash
alembic upgrade head          # apply all pending migrations
alembic downgrade -1          # roll back one migration
alembic current               # show current revision
alembic history               # show migration history
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add column"  # generate new migration
```

#### Implementation steps

1. Run `alembic init alembic` in the `backend/` directory
2. Update `alembic/env.py` to import `Base.metadata` and set the DB URL
3. Run `alembic revision --autogenerate -m 'initial schema'`
4. Open the generated file in `alembic/versions/` and review it — confirm all 5 tables appear
5. Run `alembic upgrade head`
6. Confirm tables exist: `psql postgresql://mtg:mtg@localhost:5432/mtg -c '\dt'`
7. Commit: `git commit -m 'feat: initial alembic migration'`

